    "body": "Installing a CUDA-aware MPI in the defaults, e.g. with\r\n```bash\r\nspack install mpi+cuda\r\n```\r\n\r\ndoes not properly select `openmpi+cuda` but just the plain `openmpi~cuda` default.\r\n\r\nSince \"CUDA-Awareness\" (yes/no) is a MPI property of nearly all [popular MPI implementations](https://devblogs.nvidia.com/parallelforall/introduction-cuda-aware-mpi/), it would make sense to be able to define `+cuda` as a variant of the virtual `mpi` package.\r\n\r\nCUDA Aware MPI implementations from the 2013 blog post above:\r\n\r\n    MVAPICH2 1.8/1.9b\r\n    OpenMPI 1.7 (beta)\r\n    CRAY MPI (MPT 5.6.2)\r\n    IBM Platform MPI (8.3)\r\n    SGI MPI (1.08)",
    "performed_via_github_app": null
